content:
This file defines the main layout for the dashboard section of the application. It sets up a two-column structure with a sidebar on the left and the main content area on the right.

## Key Exports/Functions/Props

*   **`DashboardLayout`**: A React functional component that serves as the layout.
    *   **`children`**: A `React.ReactNode` prop that represents the content to be rendered within the main area of the layout.

## Usage Example

This layout component is typically used in a `layout.tsx` file within a route segment (e.g., `app/dashboard/layout.tsx`) to wrap all pages within that segment. The `children` prop will automatically receive the page component for the current route.

```tsx
// app/dashboard/layout.tsx
import { Sidebar } from "@/components/ui/sidebar";
import { ToastProvider } from "@/components/ui/toast";

export default function DashboardLayout({ children }: {
  children: React.ReactNode;
}) {
  return (
    <ToastProvider>
      <div className="flex h-screen bg-background overflow-hidden">
        <Sidebar />
        <main className="flex-1 overflow-y-auto">{children}</main>
      </div>
    </ToastProvider>
  );
}

// Example usage in a page (e.g., app/dashboard/page.tsx)
// import DashboardLayout from "./layout";
